      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RODNEY OH RODNEY (5) was too good in a CL1 at Ascot last time out, leading throughout to in easily over 1000m. He comes back in grade today and that effort stands out in this field. Can repeat the dose today. SOMETHING ROYAL (2) comes here first-up and will be fitter for a recent trial. She's moved to the Regan yard since her last start at Northam in a CL3. Should get every chance and can make an impression. PLAYFUL STAR (6) returns from a spell of five-and-a-half months and is having her first run for a new yard. Finished fourth at Bunbury over 1100m when first-up last time in work. Among the better hopes while fresh. QUICK AS SILVER (3) turned in a decent effort last start to finish third over 1100m at Dongara. This looks a good race for him and there is no reason he cannot find winning ways. ALWAYS AWESOME (7) is not to be discounted first-up.",
